<h2>Medicare Coverage and Hearing Aids {#medicare-coverage-hearing-aids}</h2>
<h3>Current Medicare Coverage Status</h3>
<p>Medicare doesn&#39;t cover hearing aids or exams for fitting hearing aids. You pay 100% of the cost for hearing aids and exams. However, understanding your options is crucial:</p>
<h4><strong>Original Medicare (Parts A &amp; B):</strong></h4>
<ul>
<li>❌ Does NOT cover hearing aids</li>
<li>❌ Does NOT cover hearing aid fitting exams</li>
<li>✅ DOES cover diagnostic hearing exams if ordered by a doctor</li>
<li>✅ Covers cochlear implants when medically necessary</li>
</ul>
<h4><strong>Medicare Part C (Medicare Advantage):</strong></h4>
<p>Some Medicare Advantage Plans (Part C) offer extra benefits that Original Medicare doesn&#39;t cover - like vision, hearing, or dental</p>
<p>Many Medicare Advantage plans now include:</p>
<ul>
<li>Hearing aid allowances ($500-$3,000 per year)</li>
<li>Routine hearing exams</li>
<li>Fitting services</li>
<li>Battery allowances</li>
</ul>
